<subSubSection id="C322B8883A2AFFB3FF0AEEC8FE73FDE8" pageId="42" pageNumber="1175" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B87EB033A2AFFB3FF0AEEC8FE73FDE8" blockId="42.[178,1085,393,561]" pageId="42" pageNumber="1175">
Comment: The original description is based on 
<specimenCount id="9D3E208A3A2AFFB3FD5BEEC8FCDAFE46" box="[739,876,393,414]" pageId="42" pageNumber="1175" type="generic" typeStatus="syntypes">two syntypes</specimenCount>
of unspecified sex, one of them deposited in Museo Civico di Storia Naturale Genova and one in the Fauvel collection at the IRSNB (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA996F23A2AFFB3FE01EE82FDFFFE01" author="FAUVEL A" box="[441,585,451,473]" pageId="42" pageNumber="1175" pagination="171 - 315" refId="ref28200" refString="FAUVEL A. (1878): Les Staphylinides des Moluques et de la Nouvelle Guinee. - Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Genova 12: 171 - 315." type="journal article" year="1878">FAUVEL 1878</bibRefCitation>
). The examined female 
<typeStatus id="548355A13A2AFFB3FCFAEE85FC27FE01" box="[834,913,452,473]" pageId="42" pageNumber="1175">syntype</typeStatus>
from the Fauvel collection and the additional female from the BMNH belong to an unidentified genus of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3890803A2AFFB3FF0AEEBFFEADFDCC" authorityName="Casey" authorityYear="1905" box="[178,283,510,532]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="1175" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subTribe" subTribe="Medonina">Medonina</taxonomicName>
, certainly not to 
<taxonomicName id="4C3890803A2AFFB3FE6AEEBFFDF0FDCB" authorityName="DEJEAN" authorityYear="1833" box="[466,582,510,531]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lithocharis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="42" pageNumber="1175" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B94C37113A2AFFB3FE6AEEBFFDF0FDCB" box="[466,582,510,531]" italics="true" pageId="42" pageNumber="1175">Lithocharis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The head and the forebody of the 
<typeStatus id="548355A13A2AFFB3FC7DEEBFFBA2FDCB" box="[965,1044,510,531]" pageId="42" pageNumber="1175">syntype</typeStatus>
are illustrated in 
<figureCitation id="1303F7863A2AFFB3FE80ED5AFE77FDE8" box="[312,449,539,561]" captionStart="Figs 95-101" captionStartId="34.[178,218,1432,1454]" captionTargetBox="[184,1091,212,1409]" captionTargetId="figure-1@34.[178,1091,212,1423]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="Figs 95-101: Lithocharis inermis nov.sp. (95-99) and &quot;Lithocharis&quot; gigantea FAUVEL, syntype (100-101): (95, 100) forebody; (96) male sternite VII; (97) male sternite VIII; (98-99) aedeagus in lateral and in ventral view; head (101). Scale bars: 95, 100-101: 1.0 mm; 96-99: 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5184214" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5184214/files/figure.png" pageId="42" pageNumber="1175">Figs 100-101</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
